{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_011FXd9XUg2dGzVEXCBNHXPJ","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect. Here are all the contents of the shared crate files you requested:\n\n## `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/shared/Cargo.toml`\n\n```toml\n[package]\nname = \"rng-shared\"\nversion = \"0.1.0\"\nedition = \"2021\"\n\n[dependencies]\nanchor-lang = { workspace = true }\nsolana-sha256-hasher = { workspace = true }\n```\n\n## `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/shared/src/lib.rs`\n\n```rust\npub mod commit_reveal;\npub mod constants;\npub mod cpi;\npub mod escrow;\npub mod fees;\npub mod lifecycle;\npub mod pause;\npub mod tiers;\npub mod timeout;\n```\n\n## `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/shared/src/constants.rs`\n\n```rust\n/// Coin sides\npub const SIDE_HEADS: u8 = 0;\npub const SIDE_TAILS: u8 = 1;\n\n/// Match phases\npub const PHASE_WAITING: u8 = 0;   // Creator placed bet, waiting for opponent\npub const PHASE_LOCKED: u8 = 1;    // Both players in, requesting VRF\npub const PHASE_SETTLED: u8 = 2;   // VRF resolved, winner determined\npub const PHASE_CANCELLED: u8 = 3; // Creator cancelled before opponent joined\n\n/// Timeout (in seconds) after which a LOCKED match can be cancelled.\npub const LOCK_TIMEOUT_SECONDS: i64 = 120; // 2 minutes\n\n/// Derive a coin side (0 or 1) from a randomness byte.\npub fn from_randomness(byte: u8) -> u8 {\n    byte % 2\n}\n\n/// Returns true if the given value is a valid side (HEADS or TAILS).\npub fn is_valid_side(side: u8) -> bool {\n    side == SIDE_HEADS || side == SIDE_TAILS\n}\n\n#[cfg(test)]\nmod tests {\n    use super::*;\n\n    #[test]\n    fn test_from_randomness() {\n        assert_eq!(from_randomness(0), SIDE_HEADS);\n        assert_eq!(from_randomness(1), SIDE_TAILS);\n        assert_eq!(from_randomness(2), SIDE_HEADS);\n        assert_eq!(from_randomness(255), SIDE_TAILS);\n    }\n\n    #[test]\n    fn test_is_valid_side() {\n        assert!(is_valid_side(SIDE_HEADS));\n        assert!(is_valid_side(SIDE_TAILS));\n        assert!(!is_valid_side(2));\n        assert!(!is_valid_side(255));\n    }\n}\n```\n\n## `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/shared/src/escrow.rs`\n\n```rust\nuse anchor_lang::prelude::*;\nuse anchor_lang::system_program;\n\n/// Error codes for escrow operations.\n#[error_code]\npub enum EscrowError {\n    /// The escrow PDA does not hold enough lamports for the requested transfer.\n    #[msg(\"Insufficient escrow balance\")]\n    InsufficientEscrowBalance,\n}\n\n/// Transfers lamports from a PDA to a recipient using direct lamport manipulation.\n///\n/// This is the standard pattern for moving funds out of a program-owned PDA\n/// (e.g., paying out a winner, refunding a player, sending fees to treasury).\n///\n/// # Example\n/// ```ignore\n/// transfer_lamports_from_pda(\n///     &ctx.accounts.coinflip_match.to_account_info(),\n///     &ctx.accounts.winner.to_account_info(),\n///     payout_amount,\n/// )?;\n/// ```\npub fn transfer_lamports_from_pda(\n    pda: &AccountInfo,\n    recipient: &AccountInfo,\n    amount: u64,\n) -> Result<()> {\n    let pda_balance = pda.lamports();\n    require!(pda_balance >= amount, EscrowError::InsufficientEscrowBalance);\n\n    **pda.try_borrow_mut_lamports()? -= amount;\n    **recipient.try_borrow_mut_lamports()? += amount;\n\n    Ok(())\n}\n\n/// Transfers lamports from a signer to a PDA using system program CPI.\n///\n/// This is the standard pattern for depositing funds into an escrow PDA\n/// (e.g., a player funding a match entry).\n///\n/// # Example\n/// ```ignore\n/// transfer_lamports_to_pda(\n///     &ctx.accounts.creator.to_account_info(),\n///     &ctx.accounts.coinflip_match.to_account_info(),\n///     entry_amount,\n///     &ctx.accounts.system_program.to_account_info(),\n/// )?;\n/// ```\npub fn transfer_lamports_to_pda<'a>(\n    from: &AccountInfo<'a>,\n    pda: &AccountInfo<'a>,\n    amount: u64,\n    system_program_info: &AccountInfo<'a>,\n) -> Result<()> {\n    system_program::transfer(\n        CpiContext::new(\n            system_program_info.clone(),\n            system_program::Transfer {\n                from: from.clone(),\n                to: pda.clone(),\n            },\n        ),\n        amount,\n    )\n}\n```\n\nKey patterns observed:\n- **`AccountInfo` usage**: Both functions accept `&AccountInfo` (not `&mut AccountInfo`)\n- **Lamport transfers**: `transfer_lamports_from_pda` uses direct `**pda.try_borrow_mut_lamports()?` manipulation for PDA → recipient\n- **System program CPI**: `transfer_lamports_to_pda` uses `system_program::transfer` with `CpiContext::new` for signer → PDA\n- **Error handling**: Custom `#[error_code]` enum with `EscrowError::InsufficientEscrowBalance`\n- **Lifetime annotations**: Generic `<'a>` on `AccountInfo` parameters in CPI function"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: adb37a6dfd326c2e6 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 24681\ntool_uses: 4\nduration_ms: 14051</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"34433cb1-6ee0-432f-833f-aec143a4b7e1","uuid":"1fb7531c-21dc-491b-a532-d2fec17e506a","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"I need to understand the current state of the shared crate at `sources/rng-utopia/solana/shared/`. Please:\n\n1. Read `sources/rng-utopia/solana/shared/Cargo.toml` completely\n2. Read `sources/rng-utopia/solana/shared/src/lib.rs` completely\n3. Read `sources/rng-utopia/solana/shared/src/constants.rs` completely\n4. Read `sources/rng-utopia/solana/shared/src/escrow.rs` completely (to see patterns for AccountInfo usage)\n\nReturn ALL contents verbatim - I need exact code to understand patterns.","agentId":"adb37a6dfd326c2e6","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect. Here are all the contents of the shared crate files you requested:\n\n## `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/shared/Cargo.toml`\n\n```toml\n[package]\nname 