{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01RX2FV8ZQ3Cd91kTDeVny6B","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I've gathered all the requested files. Here's the complete contents verbatim:\n\n## 1. Cargo.toml\n```toml\n[package]\nname = \"coinflip\"\nversion = \"0.1.0\"\nedition = \"2021\"\n\n[lib]\ncrate-type = [\"cdylib\", \"lib\"]\nname = \"coinflip\"\n\n[dependencies]\nanchor-lang = { workspace = true }\nrng-shared = { workspace = true }\nplatform = { path = \"../platform\", features = [\"cpi\"] }\nephemeral-vrf-sdk = { version = \"0.2.3\", features = [\"anchor\"] }\n\n[features]\nno-entrypoint = []\nno-idl = []\nno-log-ix-name = []\ncpi = [\"no-entrypoint\"]\ndefault = [\"mock-oracle\"]\nmock-oracle = []\nidl-build = [\"anchor-lang/idl-build\"]\n```\n\n## 2. lib.rs\n```rust\nuse anchor_lang::prelude::*;\n\npub mod error;\npub mod instructions;\npub mod state;\n\nuse instructions::*;\n\ndeclare_id!(\"H8Q2R1bUxzfUkV6WRRiZxYWwGfCr794AcnskWpsRQJf3\");\n\n#[program]\npub mod coinflip {\n    use super::*;\n\n    pub fn initialize_config(\n        ctx: Context<InitializeConfig>,\n        oracle_authority: Pubkey,\n        treasury: Pubkey,\n    ) -> Result<()> {\n        instructions::initialize_config::handler(ctx, oracle_authority, treasury)\n    }\n\n    pub fn create_match(ctx: Context<CreateMatch>, tier: u8, side: u8) -> Result<()> {\n        instructions::create_match::handler(ctx, tier, side)\n    }\n\n    pub fn join_match(ctx: Context<JoinMatch>) -> Result<()> {\n        instructions::join_match::handler(ctx)\n    }\n\n    pub fn resolve_match(ctx: Context<ResolveMatch>, randomness: [u8; 32]) -> Result<()> {\n        instructions::resolve_match::handler(ctx, randomness)\n    }\n\n    pub fn claim_payout(ctx: Context<ClaimPayout>) -> Result<()> {\n        instructions::claim_payout::handler(ctx)\n    }\n\n    pub fn cancel_match(ctx: Context<CancelMatch>) -> Result<()> {\n        instructions::cancel_match::handler(ctx)\n    }\n\n    pub fn timeout_cancel(ctx: Context<TimeoutCancel>) -> Result<()> {\n        instructions::timeout_cancel::handler(ctx)\n    }\n\n    pub fn force_close(ctx: Context<ForceClose>) -> Result<()> {\n        instructions::force_close::handler(ctx)\n    }\n}\n```\n\n## 3. state.rs\n```rust\nuse anchor_lang::prelude::*;\n\n/// Global configuration for the coinflip program.\n/// PDA seeds: [b\"coinflip_config\"]\n#[account]\n#[derive(InitSpace)]\npub struct CoinflipConfig {\n    /// Admin authority (can update config).\n    pub authority: Pubkey,\n    /// Oracle authority (VRF callback signer — test keypair or MagicBlock).\n    pub oracle_authority: Pubkey,\n    /// Fee destination wallet.\n    pub treasury: Pubkey,\n    /// Bump seed for PDA derivation.\n    pub bump: u8,\n}\n\n/// A coinflip match between two players.\n/// PDA seeds: [b\"match\", creator.key().as_ref()]\n#[account]\n#[derive(InitSpace)]\npub struct CoinflipMatch {\n    /// The player who created the match.\n    pub creator: Pubkey,\n    /// The player who joined (Pubkey::default() if empty).\n    pub opponent: Pubkey,\n    /// Tier index (0-5).\n    pub tier: u8,\n    /// Entry amount in lamports (derived from tier).\n    pub entry_amount: u64,\n    /// Side chosen by creator (0 = Heads, 1 = Tails).\n    pub creator_side: u8,\n    /// Current phase of the match.\n    pub phase: u8,\n    /// The winning side after VRF resolution (0 or 1, only valid when settled).\n    pub result: u8,\n    /// The winner's pubkey (Pubkey::default() until settled).\n    pub winner: Pubkey,\n    /// Whether the payout has been claimed.\n    pub claimed: bool,\n    /// Unix timestamp when the match entered LOCKED phase (0 if still WAITING).\n    pub locked_at: i64,\n    /// Bump seed for PDA derivation.\n    pub bump: u8,\n}\n```\n\n## 4. Instructions Directory Listing\n```\ntotal 44\ndrwxr-xr-x 11 vscode vscode  352 Feb 25 09:37 .\ndrwxr-xr-x  6 vscode vscode  192 Feb 25 09:37 ..\n-rw-r--r--  1 vscode vscode 1032 Feb 25 09:37 cancel_match.rs\n-rw-r--r--  1 vscode vscode 5788 Feb 25 09:37 claim_payout.rs\n-rw-r--r--  1 vscode vscode 1892 Feb 25 09:37 create_match.rs\n-rw-r--r--  1 vscode vscode 1418 Feb 25 09:37 force_close.rs\n-rw-r--r--  1 vscode vscode  876 Feb 25 09:37 initialize_config.rs\n-rw-r--r--  1 vscode vscode 4394 Feb 25 09:37 join_match.rs\n-rw-r--r--  1 vscode vscode  387 Feb 25 09:37 mod.rs\n-rw-r--r--  1 vscode vscode 1852 Feb 25 09:37 resolve_match.rs\n-rw-r--r--  1 vscode vscode 2464 Feb 25 09:37 timeout_cancel.rs\n```\n\n## 5. join_match.rs\n```rust\nuse anchor_lang::prelude::*;\nuse anchor_lang::system_program;\nuse rng_shared::constants::{PHASE_LOCKED, PHASE_WAITING};\n\nuse ephemeral_vrf_sdk::anchor::vrf;\n#[cfg(not(feature = \"mock-oracle\"))]\nuse ephemeral_vrf_sdk::instructions::{create_request_randomness_ix, RequestRandomnessParams};\n#[cfg(not(feature = \"mock-oracle\"))]\nuse ephemeral_vrf_sdk::types::SerializableAccountMeta;\n\nuse crate::error::CoinflipError;\nuse crate::state::{CoinflipConfig, CoinflipMatch};\n\n/// Unified struct — `#[vrf]` macro adds program_identity, vrf_program,\n/// slot_hashes, and system_program. Same IDL in both build modes.\n/// In mock-oracle mode the VRF accounts are present but the CPI is skipped.\n#[vrf]\n#[derive(Accounts)]\npub struct JoinMatch<'info> {\n    /// The opponent joining the match. Must sign and fund their escrow.\n    #[account(mut)]\n    pub opponent: Signer<'info>,\n\n    /// The match PDA to join.\n    #[account(\n        mut,\n        seeds = [b\"match\", coinflip_match.creator.as_ref()],\n        bump = coinflip_match.bump,\n    )]\n    pub coinflip_match: Account<'info, CoinflipMatch>,\n\n    /// The config PDA (needed for VRF callback account metas).\n    #[account(\n        seeds = [b\"coinflip_config\"],\n        bump = config.bump,\n    )]\n    pub config: Account<'info, CoinflipConfig>,\n\n    /// CHECK: Oracle queue for VRF randomness requests.\n    #[account(mut)]\n    pub oracle_queue: AccountInfo<'info>,\n    // #[vrf] auto-adds: program_identity, vrf_program, slot_hashes, system_program\n}\n\npub fn handler(ctx: Context<JoinMatch>) -> Result<()> {\n    let coinflip_match = &ctx.accounts.coinflip_match;\n\n    // Must be in WAITING phase\n    require!(\n        coinflip_match.phase == PHASE_WAITING,\n        CoinflipError::InvalidPhase\n    );\n\n    // Opponent cannot be the creator\n    require!(\n        ctx.accounts.opponent.key() != coinflip_match.creator,\n        CoinflipError::CannotJoinOwnMatch\n    );\n\n    let entry_amount = coinflip_match.entry_amount;\n    let opponent_key = ctx.accounts.opponent.key();\n\n    // Cache keys for VRF callback before mutable borrow\n    #[cfg(not(feature = \"mock-oracle\"))]\n    let config_key = ctx.accounts.config.key();\n    #[cfg(not(feature = \"mock-oracle\"))]\n    let match_key = ctx.accounts.coinflip_match.key();\n\n    // Transfer entry_amount from opponent to match PDA (escrow)\n    system_program::transfer(\n        CpiContext::new(\n            ctx.accounts.system_program.to_account_info(),\n            system_program::Transfer {\n                from: ctx.accounts.opponent.to_account_info(),\n                to: ctx.accounts.coinflip_match.to_account_info(),\n            },\n        ),\n        entry_amount,\n    )?;\n\n    // Update match state\n    {\n        let coinflip_match = &mut ctx.accounts.coinflip_match;\n        coinflip_match.opponent = opponent_key;\n        coinflip_match.phase = PHASE_LOCKED;\n        coinflip_match.locked_at = Clock::get()?.unix_timestamp;\n    }\n\n    // Request VRF randomness (real mode only — skipped in bankrun tests)\n    #[cfg(not(feature = \"mock-oracle\"))]\n    {\n        // Anchor discriminator: sha256(\"global:resolve_match\")[..8]\n        const RESOLVE_MATCH_DISC: [u8; 8] = [73, 0, 15, 197, 178, 47, 21, 193];\n        let discriminator = RESOLVE_MATCH_DISC.to_vec();\n\n        // Use match PDA pubkey bytes as unique caller seed\n        let caller_seed = match_key.to_bytes();\n\n        let ix = create_request_randomness_ix(RequestRandomnessParams {\n            payer: ctx.accounts.opponent.key(),\n            oracle_queue: ctx.accounts.oracle_queue.key(),\n            callback_program_id: crate::ID,\n            callback_discriminator: discriminator,\n            caller_seed,\n            accounts_metas: Some(vec![\n                // resolve_match needs: oracle (auto-added by VRF), config, coinflip_match\n                SerializableAccountMeta {\n                    pubkey: config_key,\n                    is_signer: false,\n                    is_writable: false,\n                },\n                SerializableAccountMeta {\n                    pubkey: match_key,\n                    is_signer: false,\n                    is_writable: true,\n                },\n            ]),\n            callback_args: None,\n        });\n\n        ctx.accounts\n            .invoke_signed_vrf(&ctx.accounts.opponent.to_account_info(), &ix)\n            .map_err(|_| error!(CoinflipError::VrfRequestFailed))?;\n    }\n\n    Ok(())\n}\n```\n\n## 6. claim_payout.rs\n```rust\nuse anchor_lang::prelude::*;\nuse rng_shared::constants::PHASE_SETTLED;\nuse rng_shared::fees::calculate_fee;\n\nuse crate::error::CoinflipError;\nuse crate::state::{CoinflipConfig, CoinflipMatch};\n\n#[derive(Accounts)]\npub struct ClaimPayout<'info> {\n    /// Either the creator or opponent can trigger the claim.\n    #[account(mut)]\n    pub caller: Signer<'info>,\n\n    /// The winner who receives the payout.\n    /// CHECK: Validated against coinflip_match.winner in handler.\n    #[account(mut)]\n    pub winner: AccountInfo<'info>,\n\n    /// The match PDA (closed after claim — rent refunded to creator).\n    #[account(\n        mut,\n        close = creator,\n        seeds = [b\"match\", coinflip_match.creator.as_ref()],\n        bump = coinflip_match.bump,\n    )]\n    pub coinflip_match: Account<'info, CoinflipMatch>,\n\n    /// The config PDA (for treasury address + CPI signing).\n    #[account(\n        seeds = [b\"coinflip_config\"],\n        bump = config.bump,\n    )]\n    pub config: Account<'info, CoinflipConfig>,\n\n    /// The treasury account to receive fees.\n    /// CHECK: Validated against config.treasury in handler.\n    #[account(mut)]\n    pub treasury: AccountInfo<'info>,\n\n    /// The creator account (receives rent refund on close).\n    /// CHECK: Validated against coinflip_match.creator in handler.\n    #[account(mut)]\n    pub creator: AccountInfo<'info>,\n\n    /// Creator's player profile PDA on the platform program.\n    /// CHECK: Validated by platform program via CPI (if account exists).\n    #[account(mut)]\n    pub creator_profile: AccountInfo<'info>,\n\n    /// Opponent's player profile PDA on the platform program.\n    /// CHECK: Validated by platform program via CPI (if account exists).\n    #[account(mut)]\n    pub opponent_profile: AccountInfo<'info>,\n\n    /// The platform program for CPI calls.\n    pub platform_program: Program<'info, platform::program::Platform>,\n\n    pub system_program: Program<'info, System>,\n}\n\npub fn handler(ctx: Context<ClaimPayout>) -> Result<()> {\n    let coinflip_match = &ctx.accounts.coinflip_match;\n\n    // Must be in SETTLED phase\n    require!(\n        coinflip_match.phase == PHASE_SETTLED,\n        CoinflipError::InvalidPhase\n    );\n\n    // Caller must be either creator or opponent\n    let caller = ctx.accounts.caller.key();\n    require!(\n        caller == coinflip_match.creator || caller == coinflip_match.opponent,\n        CoinflipError::UnauthorizedCaller\n    );\n\n    // Validate winner account matches on-chain winner\n    require!(\n        ctx.accounts.winner.key() == coinflip_match.winner,\n        CoinflipError::NotWinner\n    );\n\n    // Prevent double claim\n    require!(!coinflip_match.claimed, CoinflipError::AlreadyClaimed);\n\n    // Validate treasury matches config\n    require!(\n        ctx.accounts.treasury.key() == ctx.accounts.config.treasury,\n        CoinflipError::InvalidPhase\n    );\n\n    // Validate creator matches match.creator\n    require!(\n        ctx.accounts.creator.key() == coinflip_match.creator,\n        CoinflipError::InvalidPhase\n    );\n\n    // Compute payout amounts\n    let pool = coinflip_match.entry_amount.checked_mul(2).unwrap();\n    let fee = calculate_fee(pool);\n    let payout = pool - fee;\n\n    // Transfer payout to winner\n    let match_info = ctx.accounts.coinflip_match.to_account_info();\n    **match_info.try_borrow_mut_lamports()? -= payout;\n    **ctx.accounts.winner.try_borrow_mut_lamports()? += payout;\n\n    // Transfer fee to treasury\n    **match_info.try_borrow_mut_lamports()? -= fee;\n    **ctx.accounts.treasury.try_borrow_mut_lamports()? += fee;\n\n    // CPI: update player profiles (only if they exist on-chain)\n    let config_bump = ctx.accounts.config.bump;\n    let signer_seeds: &[&[&[u8]]] = &[&[b\"coinflip_config\", &[config_bump]]];\n\n    let cpi_program = ctx.accounts.platform_program.to_account_info();\n\n    // Creator profile update — skip if profile hasn't been created yet\n    if !ctx.accounts.creator_profile.data_is_empty() {\n        let creator_is_winner = ctx.accounts.creator.key() == coinflip_match.winner;\n        let creator_won_amount = if creator_is_winner { payout } else { 0 };\n        let cpi_accounts_creator = platform::cpi::accounts::UpdatePlayerProfile {\n            caller: ctx.accounts.config.to_account_info(),\n            profile: ctx.accounts.creator_profile.to_account_info(),\n        };\n        let cpi_ctx_creator =\n            CpiContext::new_with_signer(cpi_program.clone(), cpi_accounts_creator, signer_seeds);\n        platform::cpi::update_player_profile(\n            cpi_ctx_creator,\n            coinflip_match.entry_amount,\n            creator_won_amount,\n            creator_is_winner,\n        )?;\n    }\n\n    // Opponent profile update — skip if profile hasn't been created yet\n    if !ctx.accounts.opponent_profile.data_is_empty() {\n        let opponent_is_winner = coinflip_match.opponent == coinflip_match.winner;\n        let opponent_won_amount = if opponent_is_winner { payout } else { 0 };\n        let cpi_accounts_opponent = platform::cpi::accounts::UpdatePlayerProfile {\n            caller: ctx.accounts.config.to_account_info(),\n            profile: ctx.accounts.opponent_profile.to_account_info(),\n        };\n        let cpi_ctx_opponent =\n            CpiContext::new_with_signer(cpi_program, cpi_accounts_opponent, signer_seeds);\n        platform::cpi::update_player_profile(\n            cpi_ctx_opponent,\n            coinflip_match.entry_amount,\n            opponent_won_amount,\n            opponent_is_winner,\n        )?;\n    }\n\n    // Account is closed by Anchor's `close = creator` constraint —\n    // remaining lamports (rent) are sent to creator, data is zeroed,\n    // and owner is set back to system program. This ensures the PDA\n    // is fully cleaned up so the creator can start a new match.\n\n    Ok(())\n}\n```\n\n## Summary of Current VRF Usage\n\nThe coinflip program currently uses **MagicBlock Ephemeral VRF** (`ephemeral-vrf-sdk` version 0.2.3) with the following integration:\n\n- **Dependency**: `ephemeral-vrf-sdk = { version = \"0.2.3\", features = [\"anchor\"] }`\n- **VRF Request Location**: Initiated in `join_match.rs` when second player joins\n- **VRF Callback Target**: `resolve_match` instruction (discriminator `[73, 0, 15, 197, 178, 47, 21, 193]`)\n- **Caller Seed**: Uses match PDA pubkey bytes as unique identifier\n- **Account Metas Passed**: config (non-writable) and match account (writable)\n- **VRF Consumption**: Happens in `resolve_match` instruction which receives randomness from VRF oracle\n- **Payout Flow**: After match is resolved via VRF callback, `claim_payout` can be called when phase is SETTLED\n- **Mock Mode**: Feature gate `mock-oracle` allows tests to skip actual VRF CPI calls while maintaining same IDL"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: ae8f4febe7c1d3ea4 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 32602\ntool_uses: 6\nduration_ms: 35952</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"34433cb1-6ee0-432f-833f-aec143a4b7e1","uuid":"fae798af-6a2f-4844-94b3-3e2537d57ee4","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"I need to understand the current VRF usage in the coinflip program. Please:\n\n1. Read `sources/rng-utopia/solana/programs/coinflip/Cargo.toml`\n2. Read `sources/rng-utopia/solana/programs/coinflip/src/lib.rs`\n3. Read `sources/rng-utopia/solana/programs/coinflip/src/state.rs`\n4. List all files in `sources/rng-utopia/solana/programs/coinflip/src/instructions/` \n5. Read `sources/rng-utopia/solana/programs/coinflip/src/instructions/join_match.rs` (to see current VRF integration)\n6. Read `sources/rng-utopia/solana/programs/coinflip/src/instructions/claim_payout.rs` (to see current VRF consumption)\n\nReturn ALL contents verbatim.","agentId":"ae8f4febe7c1d3ea4","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I've gathered all the requested files. Here's the complete contents verbatim:\n\n## 1. Cargo.toml\n```toml\n[package]\nname = \"coinflip\"\nversion = \"0.1.0\"\nedition = \"2021\"\n\n[lib]\ncrate-type = [\"cdylib\", \"lib\"]\nname = \"coinflip\"\n\n[dependencies]\nanchor-lang = { workspace = true }\nrng-shared = { workspace = true }\nplatform = { path = \"../platform\", features = [\"cpi\"] }\nephemeral-vrf-sdk = { version = \"0.2.3\", features = [\"anchor\"] }\n\n[features]\nno-entrypoint = []\nno-idl = []\nno-log-ix-name = []\ncpi = [\"no-entrypoint\"]\ndefault = [\"mock-oracle\"]\nmock-oracle = []\nidl-build = [\"anchor-lang/idl-build\"]\n```\n\n## 2. lib.rs\n```rust\nuse anchor_lang::prelude::*;\n\npub mod error;\npub mod instructions;\npub mod state;\n\nuse instructions::*;\n\ndeclare_id!(\"H8Q2R1bUxzfUkV6WRRiZxYWwGfCr794AcnskWpsRQJf3\");\n\n#[program]\npub mod coinflip {\n    use super::*;\n\n    pub fn initialize_config(\n        ctx: Context<InitializeConfig>,\n        oracle_authority: Pubkey,\n        treasury: Pubkey,\n    ) -> Result<()> {\n        instructions::initialize_config::handler(ctx, oracle_authority, treasury)\n    }\n\n    pub fn create_match(ctx: Context<CreateMatch>, tier: u8, side: u8) -> Result<()> {\n        instructions::create_match::handler(ctx, tier, side)\n    }\n\n    pub fn join_match(ctx: Context<JoinMatch>) -> Result<()> {\n        instructions::join_match::handler(ctx)\n    }\n\n    pub fn resolve_match(ctx: Context<ResolveMatch>, randomness: [u8; 32]) -> Result<()> {\n        instructions::resolve_match::handler(ctx, randomness)\n    }\n\n    pub fn claim_payout(ctx: Context<ClaimPayout>) -> Result<()> {\n        instructions::claim_payout::handler(ctx)\n    }\n\n    pub fn cancel_match(ctx: Context<CancelMatch>) -> Result<()> {\n        instructions::cancel_match::handler(ctx)\n    }\n\n    pub fn timeout_cancel(ctx: Context<TimeoutCancel>) -> Result<()> {\n        instructions::timeout_cancel::handler(ctx)\n    }\n\n    pub fn force_close(ctx: Context<ForceClose>) -> Result<()> {\n        instructions::force_close::handler(ctx)\n    }\n}\n```\n\n## 3. state.rs\n```rust\nuse anchor_lang::prelude::*;\n\n/// Global configuration for the coinflip program.\n/// PDA seeds: [b\"coinflip_config\"]\n#[account]\n#[derive(InitSpace)]\npub struct CoinflipConfig {\n    /// Admin authority (can update config).\n    pub authority: Pubkey,\n    /// Oracle authority (VRF callback signer — test keypair or MagicBlock).\n    pub oracle_authority: Pubkey,\n    /// Fee destination wallet.\n    pub treasury: Pubkey,\n    /// Bump seed for PDA derivation.\n    pub bump: u8,\n}\n\n/// A coinflip match between two players.\n/// PDA seeds: [b\"match\", creator.key().as_ref()]\n#[account]\n#[derive(InitSpace)]\npub struct CoinflipMatch {\n    /// The player who created the match.\n    pub creator: Pubkey,\n    /// The player who joined (Pubkey::default() if empty).\n    pub opponent: Pubkey,\n    /// Tier index (0-5).\n    pub tier: u8,\n    /// Entry amount in lamports (derived from tier).\n    pub entry_amount: u64,\n    /// Side chosen by creator (0 = Heads, 1 = Tails).\n    pub creator_side: u8,\n    /// Current phase of the match.\n    pub phase: u8,\n    /// The winning side after VRF resolution (0 or 1, only valid when settled).\n    pub result: u8,\n    /// The winner's pubkey (Pubkey::default() until settled).\n    pub winner: Pubkey,\n    /// Whether the payout has been claimed.\n    pub claimed: bool,\n    /// Unix timestamp when the match entered LOCKED phase (0 if still WAITING).\n    pub locked_at: i64,\n    /// Bump seed for PDA derivation.\n    pub bump: u8,\n}\n```\n\n## 4. Instructions Directory Listing\n```\ntotal 44\ndrwxr-xr-x 11 vscode vscode  352 Feb 25 09:37 .\ndrwxr-xr-x  6 vscode vscode  192 Feb 25 09:37 ..\n-rw-r--r--  1 vscode vscode 1032 Feb 25 09:37 cancel_match.rs\n-rw-r--r--  1 vscode vscode 5788 Feb 25 09:37 claim_payout.rs\n-rw-r--r--  1 vscode vscode 1892 Feb 25 09:37 create_match.rs\n-rw-r--r--  1 vscode vscode 1418 Feb 25 09:37 force_close.rs\n-rw-r--r--  1 vscode vscode  876 Feb 25 09:37 initialize_config.rs\n-rw-r--r--  1 vscode vscode 4394 Feb 25 09:37 join_match.rs\n-rw-r--r--  1 vscode vscode  387 Feb 25 09:37 mod.rs\n-rw-r--r--  1 vscode vscode 1852 Feb 25 09:37 resolve_match.rs\n-rw-r--r--  1 vscode vscode 2464 Feb 25 09:37 timeout_cancel.rs\n```\n\n## 5. join_match.rs\n```rust\nuse anchor_lang::prelude::*;\nuse anchor_lang::system_program;\nuse rng_shared::constants::{PHASE_LOCKED, PHASE_WAITING};\n\nuse ephemeral_vrf_sdk::anchor::vrf;\n#[cfg(not(feature = \"mock-oracle\"))]\nuse ephemeral_vrf_sdk::instructions::{create_request_randomness_ix, RequestRandomnessParams};\n#[cfg(not(feature = \"mock-oracle\"))]\nuse ephemeral_vrf_sdk::types::SerializableAccountMeta;\n\nuse crate::error::CoinflipError;\nuse crate::state::{CoinflipConfig, CoinflipMatch};\n\n/// Unified struct — `#[vrf]` macro adds program_identity, vrf_program,\n/// slot_hashes, and system_program. Same IDL in both build modes.\n/// In mock-oracle mode the VRF accounts are present but the CPI is skipped.\n#[vrf]\n#[derive(Accounts)]\npub struct JoinMatch<'info> {\n    /// The opponent joining the match. Must sign and fund their escrow.\n    #[account(mut)]\n    pub opponent: Signer<'info>,\n\n    /// The match PDA to join.\n    #[account(\n        mut,\n        seeds = [b\"match\", coinflip_match.creator.as_ref()],\n        bump = coinflip_match.bump,\n    )]\n    pub coinflip_match: Account<'info, CoinflipMatch>,\n\n    /// The config PDA (needed for VRF callback account metas).\n    #[account(\n        seeds = [b\"coinflip_config\"],\n        bump = config.bump,\n    )]\n    pub config: Account<'info, CoinflipConfig>,\n\n    /// CHECK: Oracle queue for VRF randomness requests.\n    #[account(mut)]\n    pub oracle_queue: AccountInfo<'info>,\n    // #[vrf] auto-adds: program_identity, vrf_program, slot_hashes, system_program\n}\n\npub fn handler(ctx: Context<JoinMatch>) -> Result<()> {\n    let coinflip_match = &ctx.accounts.coinflip_match;\n\n    // Must be in WAITING phase\n    require!(\n        coinflip_match.phase == PHASE_WAITING,\n        CoinflipError::InvalidPhase\n    );\n\n    // Opponent cannot be the creator\n    require!(\n        ctx.accounts.opponent.key() != coinflip_match.creator,\n        CoinflipError::CannotJoinOwnMatch\n    );\n\n    let entry_amount = coinflip_match.entry_amount;\n    let opponent_key = ctx.accounts.opponent.key();\n\n    // Cache keys for VRF callback before mutable borrow\n    #[cfg(not(feature = \"mock-oracle\"))]\n    let config_key = ctx.accounts.config.key();\n    #[cfg(not(feature = \"mock-oracle\"))]\n    let match_key = ctx.accounts.coinflip_match.key();\n\n    // Transfer entry_amount from opponent to match PDA (escrow)\n    system_program::transfer(\n        CpiContext::new(\n            ctx.accounts.system_program.to_account_info(),\n            system_program::Transfer {\n                from: ctx.accounts.opponent.to_account_info(),\n                to: ctx.accounts.coinflip_match.to_account_info(),\n            },\n        ),\n        entry_amount,\n    )?;\n\n    // Update match state\n    {\n        let coinflip_match = &mut ctx.accounts.coinflip_match;\n        coinflip_match.opponent = opponent_key;\n        coinflip_match.phase = PHASE_LOCKED;\n        coinflip_match.locked_at = Clock::get()?.unix_timestamp;\n    }\n\n    // Request VRF randomness (real mode only — skipped in bankrun tests)\n    #[cfg(not(feature = \"mock-oracle\"))]\n    {\n        // Anchor discriminator: sha256(\"global:resolve_match\")[..8]\n        const RESOLVE_MATCH_DISC: [u8; 8] = [73, 0, 15, 197, 178, 47, 21, 193];\n        let discriminator = RESOLVE_MATCH_DISC.to_vec();\n\n        // Use match PDA pubkey bytes as unique caller seed\n        let caller_seed = match_key.to_bytes();\n\n        let ix = create_request_randomness_ix(RequestRandomnessParams {\n            payer: ctx.accounts.opponent.key(),\n            oracle_queue: ctx.accounts.oracle_queue.key(),\n            callback_program_id: crate::ID,\n            callback_discriminator: discriminator,\n            caller_seed,\n            accounts_metas: Some(vec![\n                // resolve_match needs: oracle (auto-added by VRF), config, coinflip_match\n                SerializableAccountMeta {\n                    pubkey: config_key,\n                    is_signer: false,\n                    is_writable: false,\n                },\n                SerializableAccountMeta {\n                    pubkey: match_key,\n                    is_signer: false,\n                    is_writable: true,\n                },\n            ]),\n            callback_args: None,\n        });\n\n        ctx.accounts\n            .invoke_signed_vrf(&ctx.accounts.opponent.to_account_info(), &ix)\n            .map_err(|_| error!(CoinflipError::VrfRequestFailed))?;\n    }\n\n    Ok(())\n}\n```\n\n## 6. claim_payout.rs\n```rust\nuse anchor_lang::prelude::*;\nuse rng_shared::constants::PHASE_SETTLED;\nuse rng_shared::fees::calculate_fee;\n\nuse crate::error::CoinflipError;\nuse crate::state::{CoinflipConfig, CoinflipMatch};\n\n#[derive(Accounts)]\npub struct ClaimPayout<'info> {\n    /// Either the creator or opponent can trigger the claim.\n    #[account(mut)]\n    pub caller: Signer<'info>,\n\n    /// The winner who receives the payout.\n    /// CHECK: Validated against coinflip_match.winner in handler.\n    #[account(mut)]\n    pub winner: AccountInfo<'info>,\n\n    /// The match PDA (closed after claim — rent refunded to creator).\n    #[account(\n        mut,\n        close = creator,\n        seeds = [b\"match\", coinflip_match.creator.as_ref()],\n        bump = coinflip_match.bump,\n    )]\n    pub coinflip_match: Account<'info, CoinflipMatch>,\n\n    /// The config PDA (for treasury address + CPI signing).\n    #[account(\n        seeds = [b\"coinflip_config\"],\n        bump = config.bump,\n    )]\n    pub config: Account<'info, CoinflipConfig>,\n\n    /// The treasury account to receive fees.\n    /// CHECK: Validated against config.treasury in handler.\n    #[account(mut)]\n    pub treasury: AccountInfo<'info>,\n\n    /// The creator account (receives rent refund on close).\n    /// CHECK: Validated against coinflip_match.creator in handler.\n    #[account(mut)]\n    pub creator: AccountInfo<'info>,\n\n    /// Creator's player profile PDA on the platform program.\n    /// CHECK: Validated by platform program via CPI (if account exists).\n    #[account(mut)]\n    pub creator_profile: AccountInfo<'info>,\n\n    /// Opponent's player profile PDA on the platform program.\n    /// CHECK: Validated by platform program via CPI (if account exists).\n    #[account(mut)]\n    pub opponent_profile: AccountInfo<'info>,\n\n    /// The platform program for CPI calls.\n    pub platform_program: Program<'info, platform::program::Platform>,\n\n    pub system_program: Program<'info, System>,\n}\n\npub fn handler(ctx: Context<ClaimPayout>) -> Result<()> {\n    let coinflip_match = &ctx.accounts.coinflip_match;\n\n    // Must be in SETTLED phase\n    require!(\n        coinflip_match.phase == PHASE_SETTLED,\n        CoinflipError::InvalidPhase\n    );\n\n    // Caller must be either creator or opponent\n    let caller = ctx.accounts.caller.key();\n    require!(\n        caller == coinflip_match.creator || caller == coinflip_match.opponent,\n        CoinflipError::UnauthorizedCaller\n    );\n\n    // Validate winner account matches on-chain winner\n    require!(\n        ctx.accounts.winner.key() == coinflip_match.winner,\n        CoinflipError::NotWinner\n    );\n\n    // Prevent double claim\n    require!(!coinflip_match.claimed, CoinflipError::AlreadyClaimed);\n\n    // Validate treasury matches config\n    require!(\n        ctx.accounts.treasury.key() == ctx.accounts.config.treasury,\n        CoinflipError::InvalidPhase\n    );\n\n    // Validate creator matches match.creator\n    require!(\n        ctx.accounts.creator.key() == coinflip_match.creator,\n        CoinflipError::InvalidPhase\n    );\n\n    // Compute payout amounts\n    let pool = coinflip_match.entry_amount.checked_mul(2).unwrap();\n    let fee = calculate_fee(pool);\n    let payout = pool - fee;\n\n    // Transfer payout to winner\n    let match_info = ctx.accounts.coinflip_match.to_account_info();\n    **match_info.try_borrow_mut_lamports()? -= payout;\n    **ctx.accounts.winner.try_borrow_mut_lamports()? += payout;\n\n    // Transfer fee to treasury\n    **match_info.try_borrow_mut_lamports()? -= fee;\n    **ctx.accounts.treasury.try_borrow_mut_lamports()? += fee;\n\n    // CPI: update player profiles (only if they exist on-chain)\n    let config_bump = ctx.accounts.config.bump;\n    let signer_seeds: &[&[&[u8]]] = &[&[b\"coinflip_config\", &[config_bump]]];\n\n    let cpi_program = ctx.accounts.platform_program.to_account_info();\n\n    // Creator profile update — skip if profile hasn't been created yet\n    if !ctx.accounts.creator_profile.data_is_empty() {\n        let creator_is_winner = ctx.accounts.creator.key() == coinflip_match.winner;\n        let creator_won_amount = if creator_is_winner { payout } else { 0 };\n        let cpi_accounts_creator = platform::cpi::accounts::UpdatePlayerProfile {\n            caller: ctx.accounts.config.to_account_info(),\n            profile: ctx.accounts.creator_profile.to_account_info(),\n        };\n        let cpi_ctx_creator =\n            CpiContext::new_with_signer(cpi_program.clone(), cpi_accounts_creator, signer_seeds);\n        platform::cpi::update_player_profile(\n            cpi_ctx_creator,\n            coinflip_match.entry_amount,\n            creator_won_amount,\n            creator_is_winner,\n        )?;\n    }\n\n    // Opponent profile update — skip if profile hasn't been created yet\n    if !ctx.accounts.opponent_profile.data_is_empty() {\n        let opponent_is_winner = coinflip_match.opponent == coinflip_match.winner;\n        let opponent_won_amount = if opponent_is_winner { payout } else { 0 };\n        let cpi_accounts_opponent = platform::cpi::accounts::UpdatePlayerProfile {\n            caller: ctx.accounts.config.to_account_info(),\n            profile: ctx.accounts.opponent_profile.to_account_info(),\n        };\n        let cpi_ctx_opponent =\n            CpiContext::new_with_signer(cpi_program, cpi_accounts_opponent, signer_seeds);\n        platform::cpi::update_player_profile(\n            cpi_ctx_opponent,\n            coinflip_match.entry_amount,\n            opponent_won_amount,\n            opponent_is_winner,\n        )?;\n    }\n\n    // Account is closed by Anchor's `close = creator` constraint —\n    // remaining lamports (rent) are sent to creator, data is zeroed,\n    // and owner is set back to system program. This ensures the PDA\n    // is fully cleaned up so the creator can start a new match.\n\n    Ok(())\n}\n```\n\n## Summary of Current VRF Usage\n\nThe coinflip program currently uses **MagicBlock Ephemeral VRF** (`ephemeral-vrf-sdk` version 0.2.3) with the following integration:\n\n- **Dependency**: `ephemeral-vrf-sdk = { version = \"0.2.3\", features = [\"anchor\"] }`\n- **VRF Request Location**: Initiated in `join_match.rs` when second player joins\n- **VRF Callback Target**: `resolve_match` instruction (discriminator `[73, 0, 15, 197, 178, 47, 21, 193]`)\n- **Caller Seed**: Uses match PDA pubkey bytes as unique identifier\n- **Account Metas Passed**: config (non-writable) and match account (writable)\n- **VRF Consumption**: Happens in `resolve_match` instruction which receives randomness from VRF oracle\n- **Payout Flow**: After match is resolved via VRF callback, `claim_payout` can be called when phase is SETTLED\n- **Mock Mode**: Feature gate `mock-oracle` allows tests to skip actual VRF CPI calls while maintaining same IDL"}],"totalDurationMs":35952,"totalTokens":32602,"totalToolUseCount":6,"usage":{"input_tokens":4075,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4454,"cache_read_input_tokens":19103,"output_tokens":4970,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":4454,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
