{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01JwDxkRFFpGiGafWiQA25qw","type":"tool_result","content":"# ORAO Solana VRF: Main Types and Usage\n\n## Key Types\n\nThe crate provides several primary structures:\n\n- **RequestV2/Request**: Instructions for requesting verifiable randomness on Solana\n- **FulfillV2/Fulfill**: Instructions for fulfilling randomness requests\n- **InitNetwork/UpdateNetwork**: Administrative instructions for VRF configuration\n\n## CPI Implementation\n\nFor Cross Program Invocation, the documentation shows this pattern:\n\n```rust\nlet request_accounts = orao_solana_vrf::cpi::accounts::Request {\n    payer: ctx.accounts.player.to_account_info(),\n    network_state: ctx.accounts.config.to_account_info(),\n    treasury: ctx.accounts.treasury.to_account_info(),\n    request: ctx.accounts.request.to_account_info(),\n    system_program: ctx.accounts.system_program.to_account_info(),\n};\nlet cpi_ctx = CpiContext::new(vrf_program, request_accounts);\norao_solana_vrf::cpi::request(cpi_ctx, seed)?;\n```\n\n## Account Structures\n\n**RandomnessAccountData** (implicit): Stores the randomness request state, derived using the `RANDOMNESS_ACCOUNT_SEED` constant and a seed value.\n\n**NetworkState**: Contains VRF configuration including \"fulfillment authorities, costs, etc.\" Accessed via the `CONFIG_ACCOUNT_SEED` PDA.\n\n**Request Instruction**: Initiates randomness requests requiring payer, network state, treasury, request account, and system program accounts.\n\nUse helper functions like `randomness_account_address()` and `get_randomness()` to interact with these accounts."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01HEdZY3XjPm2YnBHKESmsur","session_id":"34433cb1-6ee0-432f-833f-aec143a4b7e1","uuid":"c8e11df2-e655-45b9-8a4e-f1ca26968646"}
