{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01SNBU82iPYDrELEYWURR4SK","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Foundations\n     2→\n     3→Cross-cutting patterns that affect every game and every package. These topics require firm decisions before Phase 1 implementation begins.\n     4→\n     5→**Status key**: `[DECIDED]` = locked, `[OPEN]` = needs discussion, `[DRAFT]` = proposal exists but not locked.\n     6→\n     7→---\n     8→\n     9→## 1) Testing Methodology `[DRAFT]`\n    10→\n    11→### Principles\n    12→- **Local-first**: All testing optimized for local dev experience. CI shape is deferred.\n    13→- **No blanket methodology**: Different features need different test approaches. Define strategy per feature/package, not one-size-fits-all.\n    14→- **Coverage guides, not gates**: Strive for coverage on critical paths but no hard thresholds that block work.\n    15→- **Zero mocks target**: Mocks are retired as real implementations land. No adapter layers or feature flags — delete the mock.\n    16→- **Test data is setup/teardown**: Each test seeds its own state (airdrop SOL, create accounts, deploy programs as needed). No shared fixtures.\n    17→\n    18→### Layers\n    19→\n    20→| Layer | Scope | Tooling | Runs Against |\n    21→|-------|-------|---------|--------------|\n    22→| Unit | State machines, payout math, fee calc, commit-reveal hashing, VRF proof validation | vitest | In-process (no chain) |\n    23→| Component | React components — structural regression | @testing-library/react + vitest (DOM snapshots) | JSDOM |\n    24→| On-chain (program) | Anchor program correctness (instructions, accounts, constraints) | bankrun | In-process simulated validator |\n    25→| Integration | Frontend ↔ chain round-trips (connect, bet, resolve, payout) | Playwright + solana-test-validator | Local validator + headless Chromium |\n    26→| Visual regression | Key pages/flows — pixel-diff to catch UI breakage | Playwright screenshot comparison | Local dev server + headless Chromium |\n    27→\n    28→### Key Decisions\n    29→- **bankrun** for pure Anchor program tests: fast, in-process, no RPC server needed. Handles account creation, program deployment, slot advancement internally.\n    30→- **solana-test-validator** for anything the frontend touches: exposes localhost RPC so the browser can connect. Setup script deploys programs + seeds accounts before tests run.\n    31→- **Playwright** over Cypress: runs headless Chromium natively in devcontainers, lighter footprint.\n    32→- **DOM snapshots** (vitest) for lightweight structural regression on components.\n    33→- **Playwright screenshot comparison** for visual regression on full pages/flows — catches design and UX breakage when adding features.\n    34→- **No Storybook**: not adding a component catalog build artifact.\n    35→\n    36→### Per-Feature Test Strategy (Define As We Go)\n    37→Not every test type applies to every feature. When implementing a feature, define which layers apply. Example thinking:\n    38→- Coinflip state machine → unit tests (vitest)\n    39→- Coinflip lobby UI → DOM snapshot + visual regression\n    40→- Coinflip VRF resolution → on-chain program test (bankrun)\n    41→- Coinflip full flow → integration (Playwright + local validator)\n    42→- Crash multiplier curve → unit test (pure math)\n    43→- Crash real-time chart → visual regression may not be meaningful (animation); consider threshold-based assertions instead\n    44→\n    45→### Open Questions (Deferred)\n    46→- CI pipeline shape: deferred until local testing is solid.\n    47→- Coverage thresholds: revisit after Phase 1 features land.\n    48→- Playwright visual regression baseline: when do we capture initial screenshots?\n    49→\n    50→---\n    51→\n    52→## 2) On-Chain Dev Loop `[DRAFT]`\n    53→\n    54→### Iteration Flow\n    55→Default loop: `anchor test` (spins up local validator → deploys programs → runs tests → tears down).\n    56→No persistent local validator during regular dev. Devnet is not the iteration target.\n    57→\n    58→### Program Architecture\n    59→Separate deployable programs per game + a platform program for shared on-chain state.\n    60→\n    61→| Program | Type | Purpose |\n    62→|---------|------|---------|\n    63→| `solana/programs/coinflip` | Deployable | Coinflip game logic, settlement |\n    64→| `solana/programs/crash` | Deployable | Crash game logic, settlement |\n    65→| `solana/programs/platform` | Deployable | Platform settings, player profiles, per-game player metadata |\n    66→| `solana/shared` | Rust lib crate (not deployed) | Escrow helpers, lifecycle state machine, timeout logic, pause controls, commit-reveal verifier, fee distribution, platform CPI helpers, tier definitions, constants |\n    67→\n    68→- Games CPI into `platform` to read settings and update player profiles after settlement.\n    69→- Each game program has its own program ID and can be deployed/upgraded independently.\n    70→- `shared` is compiled into each program at build time, not deployed on-chain. Consistency is enforced at compile time, not via CPI at runtime.\n    71→- **Lifecycle phases**: Every round follows `WAITING → ACTIVE → LOCKED → RESOLVING → SETTLED / REFUNDED`. See `docs/specs/004-shared-infrastructure/spec.md` FR-5 for invariants.\n    72→- **Claim-based payouts**: For VRF games, `claim_payout` reads the VRF result at claim time, derives the winner, and transfers funds — all in one tx. No separate settle/resolve instruction. For commit-reveal games, the server's reveal writes the outcome, then players claim. Either way, payouts are pull-based (winner calls claim). This keeps instructions small, is gas-efficient, and puts payout tx cost on the beneficiary. Same pattern for refunds. See `004-shared-infrastructure` FR-1.\n    73→- **Legacy note**: Existing `solana/` code is leftover scaffolding — does not influence future design.\n    74→\n    75→### On-Chain State (Platform Program)\n    76→- **Platform settings account**: Fee rates, pause state, global config.\n    77→- **Player profile PDA** (per wallet): Aggregate stats, history metadata.\n    78→- **Per-game player accounts**: Game-specific stats/metadata, created on first play.\n    79→\n    80→### IDL Pipeline\n    81→1. `anchor build` → generates IDL JSON in `target/idl/` + TS types in `target/types/`\n    82→2. `scripts/sync-idl` → copies generated types into a TS package (e.g. `packages/anchor-client/`)\n    83→3. Frontend imports typed program interfaces from that package.\n    84→\n    85→Script is manual (`pnpm sync-idl`), not a post-build hook.\n    86→\n    87→### Mock Retirement\n    88→Mocks are deleted as real implementations land. No adapter layers, no feature flags. When a program is deployed and testable via `anchor test`, the corresponding mock goes away.\n    89→\n    90→### Open Questions (Deferred)\n    91→- Devnet deployment strategy: deferred until local loop is solid.\n    92→- Program upgrade authority management: single key vs multisig.\n    93→\n    94→---\n    95→\n    96→## 3) Wallet Strategy `[DECIDED: wallet-adapter]`\n    97→\n    98→**Decision**: Use `@solana/wallet-adapter-react` for V1. Privy deferred to V1.5.\n    99→**Ref**: `docs/DECISIONS.md` — \"Normal Wallets First, Privy Later\"\n   100→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01HEdZY3XjPm2YnBHKESmsur","session_id":"34433cb1-6ee0-432f-833f-aec143a4b7e1","uuid":"7b4cd2ce-af3e-4ade-9605-f1af8c7ece3f"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01HEdZY3XjPm2YnBHKESmsur","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information I need. Let me compile a comprehensive report.\n\n---\n\n## Comprehensive Analysis: Orao VRF Integration\n\n### 1. CURRENT STATE - EXISTING REFERENCES\n\n**Found in codebase:**\n- `@orao-network/solana-vrf` v0.8.0 is **already in `solana/package.json`** as a devDependency\n- Currently using **MagicBlock Ephemeral VRF** (v0.2.3) as the active VRF provider in coinflip program\n- **Decision made 2026-02-25**: VRF provider = **Orao** (replaces MagicBlock) — locked per `docs/DECISIONS.md`\n- No Rust code currently using Orao SDK — only JavaScript/TypeScript SDK in node_modules\n\n**File locations:**\n- Coinflip program with ephemeral VRF: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/programs/coinflip/src/`\n- Ephemeral VRF integration: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/programs/coinflip/src/instructions/join_match.rs`\n- Current VRF state machine: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/programs/coinflip/src/state.rs`\n\n---\n\n### 2. ORAO PACKAGE INFORMATION\n\n#### JavaScript/TypeScript SDK\n**Package**: `@orao-network/solana-vrf`\n- **Current version in codebase**: 0.8.0\n- **Available versions**: 0.8.0 (checked on crates.io)\n- **Location**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/node_modules/.pnpm/@orao-network+solana-vrf@0.8.0*/`\n- **Purpose**: Client-side randomness request and fulfillment interaction\n- **Main class**: `Orao` (extends Anchor `Program<OraoVrf>`)\n- **Key exports**:\n  - `PROGRAM_ADDRESS`: `\"VRFzZoJdhFWL8rkvu87LpKM3RbcVezpMEc6X5GVDr7y\"`\n  - `PROGRAM_ID`: PublicKey instance\n  - `RANDOMNESS_ACCOUNT_SEED`: Buffer (for PDA derivation)\n  - `CONFIG_ACCOUNT_SEED`: Buffer (for network state PDA)\n  - Helper functions: `networkStateAccountAddress()`, `randomnessAccountAddress()`, `quorum()`\n\n#### Rust Crate\n**Package**: `orao-solana-vrf`\n- **Latest version available**: 0.7.0 (per cargo search)\n- **Callback variant**: `orao-solana-vrf-cb` v0.4.0 (specialized callback mode)\n- **Status**: ✅ Production-ready, available on crates.io\n- **Features**: `cpi` feature flag for Cross Program Invocation\n\n---\n\n### 3. KEY TYPES (JavaScript SDK v0.8.0)\n\n#### State Classes\n\n**NetworkState**\n```typescript\nclass NetworkState {\n  config: NetworkConfiguration;\n  numReceived: BN;\n}\n```\n- Holds VRF configuration and request counter\n- Accessed via `Orao.getNetworkState()` method\n\n**NetworkConfiguration**\n```typescript\nclass NetworkConfiguration {\n  authority: PublicKey;           // Config authority\n  treasury: PublicKey;            // SOL fee treasury\n  requestFee: BN;                 // Fee in lamports\n  fulfillmentAuthorities: PublicKey[];  // Randomness signers\n  tokenFeeConfig: OraoTokenFeeConfig | null;  // SPL token config\n}\n```\n\n**RandomnessAccountData** (Union type)\n```typescript\ntype RandomnessAccountData = RandomnessAccountDataV1 | RandomnessAccountDataV2;\n```\n- V1: Legacy randomness format (stores individual response signatures)\n- V2: Modern format (stores aggregated randomness + client PDA)\n- Both provide methods:\n  - `getSeed()`: Returns request seed (32 bytes)\n  - `getClient()`: Returns requesting program/wallet\n  - `getFulfilledRandomness()`: Returns randomness Uint8Array or null if pending\n  - `getVersion()`: Returns account version tag\n\n**FulfilledRandomnessAccountData**\n```typescript\nclass FulfilledRandomnessAccountData {\n  seed: Uint8Array;\n  randomness: Uint8Array;\n  client: PublicKey | null;    // V2 only\n  responses: RandomnessResponse[] | null;  // V1 only\n}\n```\n- Guaranteed fulfilled (throws on unfulfilled randomness)\n\n#### Request/Fulfillment Classes\n\n**RequestBuilder**\n- Fluent interface for building request instructions\n- Methods:\n  - `.payWithToken(tokenWallet)`: Pay with SPL token instead of SOL\n  - `.withComputeUnitPrice(bigint)`: Set priority fee\n  - `.withComputeUnitPriceMultiplier(number)`: Multiply median fee\n  - `.withComputeUnitLimit(number)`: Set compute limit\n  - `.build()`: Returns Anchor MethodsBuilder for `requestV2` instruction\n  - `.rpc()`: Executes and returns `[Uint8Array, string]` = `[seed, txSignature]`\n\n**FulfillBuilder**\n- Fluent interface for fulfill instructions\n- Methods similar to RequestBuilder\n- `.build(fulfillmentAuthority, signature)`: Returns MethodsBuilder\n- `.rpc(fulfillmentAuthority, signature)`: Executes fulfillment\n\n#### Helper Classes\n\n**RandomnessResponse**\n```typescript\nclass RandomnessResponse {\n  pubkey: PublicKey;      // Fulfillment authority\n  randomness: Uint8Array; // Ed25519 signature over seed\n}\n```\n\n**OraoTokenFeeConfig**\n```typescript\nclass OraoTokenFeeConfig {\n  mint: PublicKey;        // SPL token mint\n  treasury: PublicKey;    // Token treasury wallet\n  fee: BN;                // Fee in token units\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. REQUEST INSTRUCTION DETAILS\n\n#### Program Instruction: `requestV2` (Modern, v0.4.0+)\n\n**Required Accounts**:\n1. `payer` (mut, signer) — SOL/SPL token payer\n2. `networkState` (mut) — VRF configuration PDA\n3. `treasury` (mut) — SOL fee destination\n4. `request` (mut) — Randomness account PDA\n5. `systemProgram` (readonly) — Solana system program\n\n**Account Derivation**:\n```typescript\n// Network state PDA\nconst networkStateAddress = Orao.networkStateAccountAddress(VRF_PROGRAM_ID);\n\n// Randomness request account PDA\nconst randomnessAddress = Orao.randomnessAccountAddress(seed, VRF_PROGRAM_ID);\n```\n\n**Seed Format**:\n- 32 bytes (Uint8Array)\n- Can be random (SDK generates automatically) or deterministic (caller-supplied)\n- Used to derive request account PDA and prove request uniqueness\n\n**Instruction Data**:\n- Discriminator: `requestV2` (derived from IDL discriminator bytes)\n- Seed passed as part of instruction data\n\n---\n\n### 5. CPI INTEGRATION (Rust Crate)\n\n**Rust crate structure** (orao-solana-vrf v0.7.0):\n\n```rust\n// In Cargo.toml\n[dependencies]\norao-solana-vrf = { version = \"0.7.0\", features = [\"cpi\"] }\n```\n\n**CPI call pattern** (from GitHub docs.rs):\n```rust\nuse orao_solana_vrf::cpi::accounts::Request;\nuse anchor_lang::context::CpiContext;\n\nlet request_accounts = Request {\n    payer: ctx.accounts.player.to_account_info(),\n    network_state: ctx.accounts.network_state.to_account_info(),\n    treasury: ctx.accounts.treasury.to_account_info(),\n    request: ctx.accounts.request.to_account_info(),\n    system_program: ctx.accounts.system_program.to_account_info(),\n};\nlet cpi_ctx = CpiContext::new(vrf_program, request_accounts);\norao_solana_vrf::cpi::request_v2(cpi_ctx, force)?;\n```\n\n**Key constraints**:\n- VRF program ID must be declared in program IDL\n- Requires `cpi` feature flag in Cargo.toml\n- Payer must have sufficient SOL for fee + request rent\n\n---\n\n### 6. COMPARISON: MagicBlock Ephemeral vs. Orao\n\n| Aspect | MagicBlock Ephemeral | Orao |\n|--------|----------------------|------|\n| **Current Status** | Active in coinflip, v0.2.3 | Locked decision (2026-02-25), not yet integrated |\n| **Request Style** | Custom callback mechanism | Standard Anchor requestV2 instruction |\n| **Fulfillment** | VRF program invokes callback (push) | Caller polls randomness account (pull) |\n| **Seed Handling** | Caller-supplied seed (match PDA bytes) | Caller-supplied or SDK-generated seed |\n| **Response Storage** | Randomness account with response array | Randomness account with aggregated randomness |\n| **Devnet Support** | Yes, with oracle_authority config | Yes, production-ready |\n| **Rust Integration** | ephemeral-vrf-sdk v0.2.3 | orao-solana-vrf 0.7.0 with cpi feature |\n| **Account Count** | 5 (payer, identity PDA, queue, system, slot_hashes) | 5 (payer, network_state, treasury, request, system) |\n| **Fee Model** | Static request cost | Configurable SOL + optional SPL token |\n\n---\n\n### 7. INTEGRATION CHECKLIST FOR ORAO\n\n**Rust side (on-chain)**:\n- [ ] Add `orao-solana-vrf` v0.7.0 to coinflip program's Cargo.toml with `cpi` feature\n- [ ] Update `join_match` instruction to CPI into Orao `requestV2` instead of ephemeral VRF\n- [ ] Create accounts struct with: payer, network_state PDA, treasury, request PDA, system_program\n- [ ] Derive network_state and request PDAs using `orao_solana_vrf::id()` and helper functions\n- [ ] Call `orao_solana_vrf::cpi::request_v2()` with deterministic seed (match PDA or consistent hash)\n- [ ] Update `resolve_match` to poll Orao randomness account and extract fulfilled result\n- [ ] Update CoinflipConfig: replace `oracle_authority` with `vrf_treasury` (if fees go elsewhere) OR keep oracle for other purposes\n\n**TypeScript/JavaScript side (off-chain)**:\n- [ ] Import `Orao` class from `@orao-network/solana-vrf`\n- [ ] Create Orao instance: `const vrf = new Orao(provider)`\n- [ ] For monitoring: call `vrf.getRandomness(seed)` to poll until fulfilled\n- [ ] Helper: `vrf.waitFulfilled(seed)` waits for fulfillment (finalized commitment)\n- [ ] Extract randomness from `FulfilledRandomnessAccountData`\n\n**Configuration**:\n- [ ] Mainnet Orao program ID: `VRFzZoJdhFWL8rkvu87LpKM3RbcVezpMEc6X5GVDr7y`\n- [ ] Devnet: Same program ID, supported\n- [ ] Fee: Paid by payer to Orao treasury (account provided in instruction)\n\n---\n\n### 8. KEY DECISION CONTEXT\n\n**From docs/DECISIONS.md (2026-02-25)**:\n> **Decision**: Replace MagicBlock Ephemeral VRF with **Orao** as the single VRF provider for V1.\n> **Rationale**: Orao proved straightforward devnet integration and fast fulfillment in live smoke tests. This gives us one VRF integration path for Coinflip and Lord of RNGs while preserving the pivot architecture.\n\n**Applies to**:\n- Coinflip: VRF seed generation for match settlement\n- Lord of the RNGs: Same VRF mechanism\n- Crash: VRF seed for initial server result (+ commit-reveal for verification)\n\n---\n\n### 9. FILE PATHS (ABSOLUTE)\n\n**TypeScript SDK in node_modules**:\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/node_modules/.pnpm/@orao-network+solana-vrf@0.8.0_bufferutil@4.1.0_typescript@5.9.3_utf-8-validate@5.0.10/node_modules/@orao-network/solana-vrf/dist/index.d.ts`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/node_modules/.pnpm/@orao-network+solana-vrf@0.8.0_bufferutil@4.1.0_typescript@5.9.3_utf-8-validate@5.0.10/node_modules/@orao-network/solana-vrf/dist/state.d.ts`\n- README: `.../@orao-network/solana-vrf/README.md`\n\n**Current Ephemeral VRF Rust SDK**:\n- `/home/vscode/.cargo/registry/src/index.crates.io-1949cf8c6b5b557f/ephemeral-vrf-sdk-0.2.3/src/instructions.rs`\n- `/home/vscode/.cargo/registry/src/index.crates.io-1949cf8c6b5b557f/ephemeral-vrf-sdk-0.2.3/src/anchor.rs`\n- `/home/vscode/.cargo/registry/src/index.crates.io-1949cf8c6b5b557f/ephemeral-vrf-sdk-0.2.3/src/consts.rs`\n\n**Current Integration**:\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/programs/coinflip/src/instructions/join_match.rs` — ephemeral VRF request\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/programs/coinflip/src/instructions/resolve_match.rs` — result handling\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/programs/coinflip/src/state.rs` — match and config state\n\n**Decision docs**:\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/docs/DECISIONS.md` — line 59-64 (Orao decision, locked)\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/docs/FOUNDATIONS.md` — on-chain dev loop and testing strategy\n\n---\n\n### 10. NEXT STEPS FOR IMPLEMENTATION\n\n1. **Update Cargo.toml**: Add `orao-solana-vrf = \"0.7.0\"` with `features = [\"cpi\"]` to coinflip program\n2. **Refactor join_match**: Replace ephemeral-vrf SDK calls with orao-solana-vrf CPI\n3. **Update accounts struct**: Add network_state, treasury, request account derivations\n4. **Refactor resolve_match**: Read from Orao randomness account instead of callback parameter\n5. **Update config state**: Adjust oracle_authority field or add vrf-specific config\n6. **Test integration**: Run `anchor test --skip-local-validator` with bankrun to verify CPI flow\n7. **Devnet validation**: Smoke test on devnet with live Orao program\n\nThis gives a complete, production-ready migration path from MagicBlock Ephemeral VRF to Orao, aligned with the locked architecture decision."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a16e42df7568f78f9 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 57495\ntool_uses: 35\nduration_ms: 132249</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"34433cb1-6ee0-432f-833f-aec143a4b7e1","uuid":"b02d6a15-6ad6-43e2-8461-66d2af60d2c8","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Search the codebase for any existing references to \"orao\" to understand if there's already partial integration. Also search for \"ephemeral-vrf\" and \"MagicBlock\" to understand current VRF state.\n\nThen search crates.io or docs for orao-solana-vrf to understand:\n1. The latest version available\n2. The `cpi` feature flag\n3. Key types: `RandomnessAccountData`, `NetworkState`, and the instruction for requesting randomness\n4. How to CPI into Orao's request instruction\n\nTry: `grep -r \"orao\" sources/rng-utopia/solana/` and `grep -r \"ephemeral.vrf\" sources/rng-utopia/solana/`\n\nAlso check what's on crates.io for `orao-solana-vrf` - look at version, features, and API.","agentId":"a16e42df7568f78f9","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information I need. Let me compile a comprehensive report.\n\n---\n\n## Comprehensive Analysis: Orao VRF Integration\n\n### 1. CURRENT STATE - EXISTING REFERENCES\n\n**Found in codebase:**\n- `@orao-network/solana-vrf` v0.8.0 is **already in `solana/package.json`** as a devDependency\n- Currently using **MagicBlock Ephemeral VRF** (v0.2.3) as the active VRF provider in coinflip program\n- **Decision made 2026-02-25**: VRF provider = **Orao** (replaces MagicBlock) — locked per `docs/DECISIONS.md`\n- No Rust code currently using Orao SDK — only JavaScript/TypeScript SDK in node_modules\n\n**File locations:**\n- Coinflip program with ephemeral VRF: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/programs/coinflip/src/`\n- Ephemeral VRF integration: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/programs/coinflip/src/instructions/join_match.rs`\n- Current VRF state machine: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/programs/coinflip/src/state.rs`\n\n---\n\n### 2. ORAO PACKAGE INFORMATION\n\n#### JavaScript/TypeScript SDK\n**Package**: `@orao-network/solana-vrf`\n- **Current version in codebase**: 0.8.0\n- **Available versions**: 0.8.0 (checked on crates.io)\n- **Location**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/node_modules/.pnpm/@orao-network+solana-vrf@0.8.0*/`\n- **Purpose**: Client-side randomness request and fulfillment interaction\n- **Main class**: `Orao` (extends Anchor `Program<OraoVrf>`)\n- **Key exports**:\n  - `PROGRAM_ADDRESS`: `\"VRFzZoJdhFWL8rkvu87LpKM3RbcVezpMEc6X5GVDr7y\"`\n  - `PROGRAM_ID`: PublicKey instance\n  - `RANDOMNESS_ACCOUNT_SEED`: Buffer (for PDA derivation)\n  - `CONFIG_ACCOUNT_SEED`: Buffer (for network state PDA)\n  - Helper functions: `networkStateAccountAddress()`, `randomnessAccountAddress()`, `quorum()`\n\n#### Rust Crate\n**Package**: `orao-solana-vrf`\n- **Latest version available**: 0.7.0 (per cargo search)\n- **Callback variant**: `orao-solana-vrf-cb` v0.4.0 (specialized callback mode)\n- **Status**: ✅ Production-ready, available on crates.io\n- **Features**: `cpi` feature flag for Cross Program Invocation\n\n---\n\n### 3. KEY TYPES (JavaScript SDK v0.8.0)\n\n#### State Classes\n\n**NetworkState**\n```typescript\nclass NetworkState {\n  config: NetworkConfiguration;\n  numReceived: BN;\n}\n```\n- Holds VRF configuration and request counter\n- Accessed via `Orao.getNetworkState()` method\n\n**NetworkConfiguration**\n```typescript\nclass NetworkConfiguration {\n  authority: PublicKey;           // Config authority\n  treasury: PublicKey;            // SOL fee treasury\n  requestFee: BN;                 // Fee in lamports\n  fulfillmentAuthorities: PublicKey[];  // Randomness signers\n  tokenFeeConfig: OraoTokenFeeConfig | null;  // SPL token config\n}\n```\n\n**RandomnessAccountData** (Union type)\n```typescript\ntype RandomnessAccountData = RandomnessAccountDataV1 | RandomnessAccountDataV2;\n```\n- V1: Legacy randomness format (stores individual response signatures)\n- V2: Modern format (stores aggregated randomness + client PDA)\n- Both provide methods:\n  - `getSeed()`: Returns request seed (32 bytes)\n  - `getClient()`: Returns requesting program/wallet\n  - `getFulfilledRandomness()`: Returns randomness Uint8Array or null if pending\n  - `getVersion()`: Returns account version tag\n\n**FulfilledRandomnessAccountData**\n```typescript\nclass FulfilledRandomnessAccountData {\n  seed: Uint8Array;\n  randomness: Uint8Array;\n  client: PublicKey | null;    // V2 only\n  responses: RandomnessResponse[] | null;  // V1 only\n}\n```\n- Guaranteed fulfilled (throws on unfulfilled randomness)\n\n#### Request/Fulfillment Classes\n\n**RequestBuilder**\n- Fluent interface for building request instructions\n- Methods:\n  - `.payWithToken(tokenWallet)`: Pay with SPL token instead of SOL\n  - `.withComputeUnitPrice(bigint)`: Set priority fee\n  - `.withComputeUnitPriceMultiplier(number)`: Multiply median fee\n  - `.withComputeUnitLimit(number)`: Set compute limit\n  - `.build()`: Returns Anchor MethodsBuilder for `requestV2` instruction\n  - `.rpc()`: Executes and returns `[Uint8Array, string]` = `[seed, txSignature]`\n\n**FulfillBuilder**\n- Fluent interface for fulfill instructions\n- Methods similar to RequestBuilder\n- `.build(fulfillmentAuthority, signature)`: Returns MethodsBuilder\n- `.rpc(fulfillmentAuthority, signature)`: Executes fulfillment\n\n#### Helper Classes\n\n**RandomnessResponse**\n```typescript\nclass RandomnessResponse {\n  pubkey: PublicKey;      // Fulfillment authority\n  randomness: Uint8Array; // Ed25519 signature over seed\n}\n```\n\n**OraoTokenFeeConfig**\n```typescript\nclass OraoTokenFeeConfig {\n  mint: PublicKey;        // SPL token mint\n  treasury: PublicKey;    // Token treasury wallet\n  fee: BN;                // Fee in token units\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. REQUEST INSTRUCTION DETAILS\n\n#### Program Instruction: `requestV2` (Modern, v0.4.0+)\n\n**Required Accounts**:\n1. `payer` (mut, signer) — SOL/SPL token payer\n2. `networkState` (mut) — VRF configuration PDA\n3. `treasury` (mut) — SOL fee destination\n4. `request` (mut) — Randomness account PDA\n5. `systemProgram` (readonly) — Solana system program\n\n**Account Derivation**:\n```typescript\n// Network state PDA\nconst networkStateAddress = Orao.networkStateAccountAddress(VRF_PROGRAM_ID);\n\n// Randomness request account PDA\nconst randomnessAddress = Orao.randomnessAccountAddress(seed, VRF_PROGRAM_ID);\n```\n\n**Seed Format**:\n- 32 bytes (Uint8Array)\n- Can be random (SDK generates automatically) or deterministic (caller-supplied)\n- Used to derive request account PDA and prove request uniqueness\n\n**Instruction Data**:\n- Discriminator: `requestV2` (derived from IDL discriminator bytes)\n- Seed passed as part of instruction data\n\n---\n\n### 5. CPI INTEGRATION (Rust Crate)\n\n**Rust crate structure** (orao-solana-vrf v0.7.0):\n\n```rust\n// In Cargo.toml\n[dependencies]\norao-solana-vrf = { version = \"0.7.0\", features = [\"cpi\"] }\n```\n\n**CPI call pattern** (from GitHub docs.rs):\n```rust\nuse orao_solana_vrf::cpi::accounts::Request;\nuse anchor_lang::context::CpiContext;\n\nlet request_accounts = Request {\n    payer: ctx.accounts.player.to_account_info(),\n    network_state: ctx.accounts.network_state.to_account_info(),\n    treasury: ctx.accounts.treasury.to_account_info(),\n    request: ctx.accounts.request.to_account_info(),\n    system_program: ctx.accounts.system_program.to_account_info(),\n};\nlet cpi_ctx = CpiContext::new(vrf_program, request_accounts);\norao_solana_vrf::cpi::request_v2(cpi_ctx, force)?;\n```\n\n**Key constraints**:\n- VRF program ID must be declared in program IDL\n- Requires `cpi` feature flag in Cargo.toml\n- Payer must have sufficient SOL for fee + request rent\n\n---\n\n### 6. COMPARISON: MagicBlock Ephemeral vs. Orao\n\n| Aspect | MagicBlock Ephemeral | Orao |\n|--------|----------------------|------|\n| **Current Status** | Active in coinflip, v0.2.3 | Locked decision (2026-02-25), not yet integrated |\n| **Request Style** | Custom callback mechanism | Standard Anchor requestV2 instruction |\n| **Fulfillment** | VRF program invokes callback (push) | Caller polls randomness account (pull) |\n| **Seed Handling** | Caller-supplied seed (match PDA bytes) | Caller-supplied or SDK-generated seed |\n| **Response Storage** | Randomness account with response array | Randomness account with aggregated randomness |\n| **Devnet Support** | Yes, with oracle_authority config | Yes, production-ready |\n| **Rust Integration** | ephemeral-vrf-sdk v0.2.3 | orao-solana-vrf 0.7.0 with cpi feature |\n| **Account Count** | 5 (payer, identity PDA, queue, system, slot_hashes) | 5 (payer, network_state, treasury, request, system) |\n| **Fee Model** | Static request cost | Configurable SOL + optional SPL token |\n\n---\n\n### 7. INTEGRATION CHECKLIST FOR ORAO\n\n**Rust side (on-chain)**:\n- [ ] Add `orao-solana-vrf` v0.7.0 to coinflip program's Cargo.toml with `cpi` feature\n- [ ] Update `join_match` instruction to CPI into Orao `requestV2` instead of ephemeral VRF\n- [ ] Create accounts struct with: payer, network_state PDA, treasury, request PDA, system_program\n- [ ] Derive network_state and request PDAs using `orao_solana_vrf::id()` and helper functions\n- [ ] Call `orao_solana_vrf::cpi::request_v2()` with deterministic seed (match PDA or consistent hash)\n- [ ] Update `resolve_match` to poll Orao randomness account and extract fulfilled result\n- [ ] Update CoinflipConfig: replace `oracle_authority` with `vrf_treasury` (if fees go elsewhere) OR keep oracle for other purposes\n\n**TypeScript/JavaScript side (off-chain)**:\n- [ ] Import `Orao` class from `@orao-network/solana-vrf`\n- [ ] Create Orao instance: `const vrf = new Orao(provider)`\n- [ ] For monitoring: call `vrf.getRandomness(seed)` to poll until fulfilled\n- [ ] Helper: `vrf.waitFulfilled(seed)` waits for fulfillment (finalized commitment)\n- [ ] Extract randomness from `FulfilledRandomnessAccountData`\n\n**Configuration**:\n- [ ] Mainnet Orao program ID: `VRFzZoJdhFWL8rkvu87LpKM3RbcVezpMEc6X5GVDr7y`\n- [ ] Devnet: Same program ID, supported\n- [ ] Fee: Paid by payer to Orao treasury (account provided in instruction)\n\n---\n\n### 8. KEY DECISION CONTEXT\n\n**From docs/DECISIONS.md (2026-02-25)**:\n> **Decision**: Replace MagicBlock Ephemeral VRF with **Orao** as the single VRF provider for V1.\n> **Rationale**: Orao proved straightforward devnet integration and fast fulfillment in live smoke tests. This gives us one VRF integration path for Coinflip and Lord of RNGs while preserving the pivot architecture.\n\n**Applies to**:\n- Coinflip: VRF seed generation for match settlement\n- Lord of the RNGs: Same VRF mechanism\n- Crash: VRF seed for initial server result (+ commit-reveal for verification)\n\n---\n\n### 9. FILE PATHS (ABSOLUTE)\n\n**TypeScript SDK in node_modules**:\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/node_modules/.pnpm/@orao-network+solana-vrf@0.8.0_bufferutil@4.1.0_typescript@5.9.3_utf-8-validate@5.0.10/node_modules/@orao-network/solana-vrf/dist/index.d.ts`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/node_modules/.pnpm/@orao-network+solana-vrf@0.8.0_bufferutil@4.1.0_typescript@5.9.3_utf-8-validate@5.0.10/node_modules/@orao-network/solana-vrf/dist/state.d.ts`\n- README: `.../@orao-network/solana-vrf/README.md`\n\n**Current Ephemeral VRF Rust SDK**:\n- `/home/vscode/.cargo/registry/src/index.crates.io-1949cf8c6b5b557f/ephemeral-vrf-sdk-0.2.3/src/instructions.rs`\n- `/home/vscode/.cargo/registry/src/index.crates.io-1949cf8c6b5b557f/ephemeral-vrf-sdk-0.2.3/src/anchor.rs`\n- `/home/vscode/.cargo/registry/src/index.crates.io-1949cf8c6b5b557f/ephemeral-vrf-sdk-0.2.3/src/consts.rs`\n\n**Current Integration**:\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/programs/coinflip/src/instructions/join_match.rs` — ephemeral VRF request\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/programs/coinflip/src/instructions/resolve_match.rs` — result handling\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/programs/coinflip/src/state.rs` — match and config state\n\n**Decision docs**:\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/docs/DECISIONS.md` — line 59-64 (Orao decision, locked)\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/docs/FOUNDATIONS.md` — on-chain dev loop and testing strategy\n\n---\n\n### 10. NEXT STEPS FOR IMPLEMENTATION\n\n1. **Update Cargo.toml**: Add `orao-solana-vrf = \"0.7.0\"` with `features = [\"cpi\"]` to coinflip program\n2. **Refactor join_match**: Replace ephemeral-vrf SDK calls with orao-solana-vrf CPI\n3. **Update accounts struct**: Add network_state, treasury, request account derivations\n4. **Refactor resolve_match**: Read from Orao randomness account instead of callback parameter\n5. **Update config state**: Adjust oracle_authority field or add vrf-specific config\n6. **Test integration**: Run `anchor test --skip-local-validator` with bankrun to verify CPI flow\n7. **Devnet validation**: Smoke test on devnet with live Orao program\n\nThis gives a complete, production-ready migration path from MagicBlock Ephemeral VRF to Orao, aligned with the locked architecture decision."}],"totalDurationMs":132249,"totalTokens":57495,"totalToolUseCount":35,"usage":{"input_tokens":6,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3934,"cache_read_input_tokens":49548,"output_tokens":4007,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":3934,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"