ature for `request_v2`. Setting up the CPI context with the required accounts...\n\nActually, let me take a more practical approach: I'll add the orao dependency to the workspace and shared crate with optional features, create the vrf module, and try building to see what the actual signature expects. The tricky part is deciding whether to gate orao-solana-vrf behind the mock-vrf feature—if mock-vrf is enabled, the request becomes a no-op, so I probably don't need the dependency at all in that case. I think the simplest approach is to keep `orao-solana-vrf` as a regular dependency and use conditional compilation to switch behavior based on the `mock-vrf` feature flag—real Orao CPI calls and account reading when the flag is off, no-op and simple test account reads when it's on. Let me check the Orao crate's current API and see what I'm working with.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":12235,"cache_read_input_tokens":39949,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":12235},"output_tokens":9,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"34433cb1-6ee0-432f-833f-aec143a4b7e1","uuid":"d16c9fb6-9187-4bd6-9ef3-88754a2653ab"}
