{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01Y1xAhD3jVf4tFecTvhF6v3","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01MyqxCi8GkAp3NKf1xEFreL","name":"WebFetch","input":{"url":"https://docs.rs/orao-solana-vrf/0.7.0/orao_solana_vrf/","prompt":"Give me all the key types, structs, and functions in this crate. I need:\n1. The `state` module types (especially RandomnessAccountData, Randomness, NetworkState)\n2. The `cpi` module types and functions (especially accounts::RequestV2 or Request, and request_v2)\n3. The program ID constant\n4. Any seed/PDA derivation helpers\n5. How randomness data is stored (field names, types, byte layout)\n\nBe very detailed about function signatures, struct fields, and module paths."},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2425,"cache_read_input_tokens":52184,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2425},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"34433cb1-6ee0-432f-833f-aec143a4b7e1","uuid":"b8ab72fd-5fe6-4ea9-8910-6983e4a4960c"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01MyqxCi8GkAp3NKf1xEFreL","type":"tool_result","content":"# ORAO Solana VRF Crate - Key Types and Functions\n\nBased on the documentation page provided, here's what's available:\n\n## Program ID\n- `ID` (static): The program identifier\n- `ID_CONST` (constant): Const version of ID\n- `id()` and `id_const()` functions available\n\n## Seeds & PDA Helpers\n- `CONFIG_ACCOUNT_SEED`: Seed for network-wide configuration PDA\n- `RANDOMNESS_ACCOUNT_SEED`: Seed for request/fulfillment accounts\n- `network_state_account_address()` function: Derives VRF config address\n- `randomness_account_address()` function: Derives randomness request address from seed and VRF address\n\n## State Module\nThe `state` module exists but specific type details aren't shown in this excerpt. The documentation references these as important:\n- Randomness account data structures\n- Network state configuration\n\n## Key Structs (Request/Fulfill Instructions)\n\n**Deprecated V1:**\n- `Request` (deprecated, use RequestV2)\n- `Fulfill` (deprecated, use FulfillV2)\n\n**Current V2:**\n- `RequestV2`: \"Request randomness\" instruction\n- `FulfillV2`: \"Fulfill randomness (v2)\" instruction\n- Associated `*Bumps` structs for PDA bump seeds\n\n**Builders (SDK feature):**\n- `RequestBuilder`: Constructs RequestV2 instructions\n- `FulfillBuilder`: Constructs Fulfill/FulfillV2 instructions\n\n## Helper Functions\n- `get_randomness()` (sdk): Fetches randomness request state\n- `get_network_state()` (sdk): Fetches on-chain VRF state\n- `wait_fulfilled()` (sdk): Polls until randomness is fulfilled\n- `majority()` and `quorum()`: Byzantine fault tolerance helpers\n- `xor_array()`: XOR utility function\n\n## CPI Support\nThe crate supports Cross Program Invocation with a `cpi` module (requires `cpi` feature enabled, `sdk` disabled). Exact account structures aren't detailed in this excerpt.\n\n**Note:** Detailed field names, byte layouts, and complete type definitions for state structs require viewing the actual module source code."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"34433cb1-6ee0-432f-833f-aec143a4b7e1","uuid":"26e9fc7f-70d9-4aee-a2c4-082f095f9ead","tool_use_result":{"bytes":33452,"code":200,"codeText":"","result":"# ORAO Solana VRF Crate - Key Types and Functions\n\nBased on the documentation page provided, here's what's available:\n\n## Program ID\n- `ID` (static): The program identifier\n- `ID_CONST` (constant): Const version of ID\n- `id()` and `id_const()` functions available\n\n## Seeds & PDA Helpers\n- `CONFIG_ACCOUNT_SEED`: Seed for network-wide configuration PDA\n- `RANDOMNESS_ACCOUNT_SEED`: Seed for request/fulfillment accounts\n- `network_state_account_address()` function: Derives VRF config address\n- `randomness_account_address()` function: Derives randomness request address from seed and VRF address\n\n## State Module\nThe `state` module exists but specific type details aren't shown in this excerpt. The documentation references these as important:\n- Randomness account data structures\n- Network state configuration\n\n## Key Structs (Request/Fulfill Instructions)\n\n**Deprecated V1:**\n- `Request` (deprecated, use RequestV2)\n- `Fulfill` (deprecated, use FulfillV2)\n\n**Current V2:**\n- `RequestV2`: \"Request randomness\" instruction\n- `FulfillV2`: \"Fulfill randomness (v2)\" instruction\n- Associated `*Bumps` structs for PDA bump seeds\n\n**Builders (SDK feature):**\n- `RequestBuilder`: Constructs RequestV2 instructions\n- `FulfillBuilder`: Constructs Fulfill/FulfillV2 instructions\n\n## Helper Functions\n- `get_randomness()` (sdk): Fetches randomness request state\n- `get_network_state()` (sdk): Fetches on-chain VRF state\n- `wait_fulfilled()` (sdk): Polls until randomness is fulfilled\n- `majority()` and `quorum()`: Byzantine fault tolerance helpers\n- `xor_array()`: XOR utility function\n\n## CPI Support\nThe crate supports Cross Program Invocation with a `cpi` module (requires `cpi` feature enabled, `sdk` disabled). Exact account structures aren't detailed in this excerpt.\n\n**Note:** Detailed field names, byte layouts, and complete type definitions for state structs require viewing the actual module source code.","durationMs":7713,"url":"https://docs.rs/orao-solana-vrf/0.7.0/orao_solana_vrf/"}}
